data.title: Frank Jacquez appointed as Senior Director of Learning and Enablement at BCN for business customers.
data.description: In Boca Raton, Florida on February 26, 2026, BCN introduced Frank Jacquez as the new Senior Director of Learning and Enablement. BCN specializes in managed network and technology services for businesses. Jacquez will oversee the development of a revamped Learning and Enablement department within the company. This move signifies BCN's commitment to enhancing employee training and knowledge.

data.title: MP Materials is setting up "10X" rare earth magnet manufacturing campus on 120-acre site in Northlake, Texas, less than 10 miles from its Independence facility in Fort Worth, cementing North Texas as U.S. rare earth magnet hub. #MP #rareearth
data.description: In Northlake, Texas, MP Materials Corp. revealed its choice of a 120-acre location for the development of "10X," the company's upcoming rare earth magnet manufacturing campus. This site is situated near MP's current Independence facility in Fort Worth, less than 10 miles away. 10X aims to solidify North Texas as the focal point for the U.S.'s rare earth magnet supply chain. The project will substantially enhance MP's integrated U.S. rare earth magnet production capabilities.

data.title: Analysts reduced Snowflake forecasts following Q4 results; Revenue at $1.28B, earnings at 34 cents/share, expects $1.26-1.27B revenue in Q1.
data.description: Snowflake Inc (NYSE: SNOW) exceeded expectations with its fourth-quarter fiscal 2026 financial results. The company reported revenue of $1.28 billion, surpassing analyst estimates of $1.26 billion. Additionally, Snowflake achieved adjusted earnings of 34 cents per share, exceeding predictions of 27 cents per share. CEO Sridhar Ramaswamy expressed how the past year has been transformative for all businesses, with Snowflake playing a pivotal role in the enterprise AI revolution. Looking ahead, Snowflake projects first-quarter product revenue between $1.26 billion and $1.27 billion, indicating a 27% increase compared to the previous year. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Altrata study shows how tenure, deal experience & sector expertise impact leadership teams in PE-owned businesses. NY, Feb 26, 2026 /PRNewswire.
data.description: A recent extensive study by Altrata explores the impact of factors such as hiring practices, length of employment, previous deal involvement, and industry knowledge on the makeup of leadership teams in companies owned by private equity firms. This study, the largest of its kind, provides insights into the dynamics of leadership teams. The research was conducted by Altrata, a reputable company known for its expertise in executive and wealth management. The findings were unveiled in New York on February 26, 2026. This study offers valuable information for businesses navigating the private equity landscape.
